![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The `from_config` method signature has been changed to require `reverse_param_names_mapping`, but other call sites in `quantization_utils.py` (e.g., lines 154 and 191) still pass only one argument. This will lead to a `TypeError` at runtime when loading ModelSlim configurations through those paths. Adding a default value of `None` maintains compatibility with the base class interface and existing call sites.

```python
    def from_config(
        cls, config: Dict[str, Any], reverse_param_names_mapping: dict = None
    ) -> ModelSlimConfig:
        return cls(config, reverse_param_names_mapping)
```

![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The current import structure still leaves a global import of `fused_moe` from `triton_utils` at line 50. This is problematic for NPU devices because:
1. It is redundant as it gets overwritten here.
2. If `triton_utils` or its dependencies (like `triton`) are not available on the NPU environment, the model will fail to import before reaching this hardware check.

It is recommended to move the Triton-based import into an `else` block here and remove the global import at line 50.

```suggestion
if _is_npu:
    from sglang.srt.hardware_backend.npu.quantization.fused_moe_method_npu import (
        fused_moe_npu as fused_moe,
    )
else:
    from sglang.srt.layers.moe.moe_runner.triton_utils import fused_moe
```
